<title type="html"><![CDATA[NES in a ZX Spectrum]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4504&amp;p=39157#p39157"><![CDATA[
Here`s something little I was building these days. I have two spectrums in my computer junk, one is working and the other one has broken keyboard flat connector which cannot be repaired (that was the common problem those days), so I decided to reanimate the dead one and put Nes-famicom inside it. The one I used is well known Chinese nes on a chip but with a bigger board - also known as ``Terminator``. <br /><br /> <img src="http://img360.imageshack.us/img360/4111/24102008202hh9.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Here`s what`s inside the spectrum....<br /><br /><img src="http://img233.imageshack.us/img233/8751/24102008198rf0.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><img src="http://img233.imageshack.us/img233/5520/24102008199dk2.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />I didn`t modify case at all, the cartridge slot fits perfectly where spectrum interface used to be, audio and video out fits too....<br /><br /><img src="http://img73.imageshack.us/img73/3484/24102008204qt9.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />And for the joypads I made external interface using famicom cartridge housing. It`s also possible to use two kind of joypads, the ones with 15 pin and a 9 pin connectors. Power and reset button are also placed here including the indicator led....For power supply I`m using nokia phone charger since it`s very small and provides enough current and a stable voltage....<br /><br /><img src="http://img512.imageshack.us/img512/5313/24102008196sk2.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><img src="http://img151.imageshack.us/img151/5974/24102008197lm8.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><img src="http://img384.imageshack.us/img384/5871/24102008195ii9.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />There`s nothing without the fancy blue led....<br /><br /><img src="http://img512.imageshack.us/img512/2048/24102008208tc8.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><img src="http://img385.imageshack.us/img385/6831/24102008212ez9.jpg" alt="Image" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3710"